fields.description:
When writing a Groovy script expression, for example as a conditional for a transition from the JMWE add-on, it is possible to change internal JIRA things such as the name of statuses or issue types. This can be done just by testing a script.

For example, if you just write the following groovy script and test it:
{noformat}
issue.issueType.name = "something"
{noformat}

Note the single '='. It will actually change the name of the issue type in JIRA to "something". This doesn't always show, for example looking at the issue screen, the normal name is shown, but when searching for the issues and using JQL 'type = "something"' it will find all the issues that had the same issue type.

The same can be done for example for status names:
{noformat}
issue.status.name = "whatever"
{noformat}

It is very easy to make JIRA behave very strangely when doing this. It may be that it is only changing things in memory, and restarting JIRA would resolve it, but it is still very confusing, and it's easy to make a mistake like that.

These values should be read-only from the add-on scripts.

h3. Problem Definition:
The KB *[Advanced searching - operators reference | https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRASOFTWARESERVER/Advanced+searching+-+operators+reference]*   For the *DOES NOT CONTAIN: !~* operator variable there  needs to be clarification on the results of EMPTY values, all the other NOT reference examples (!= , NOT IN, IS NOT, WAS NOT, WAS NOT IN) include this information to include the EMPTY set just not for the !~ section

For the The Example:
{quote}
Note that for version fields, the ~ operator returns an exact match. For example, to find issues where Fix Version is not "9.0", you would use the following query:
{code}
fixVersion !~ "9.0"
{code}
{quote}
This JQL Would be any issue that has a value in the fix version field that is not 9.0 but would not include issue where the FixVersion field was empty to do this the Filter would need to include:
{code}
fixVersion !~ "9.0" OR fixVersion is empty
{code}

The main take away is that when you are using a Exclude statement in JQL the Logic is such that a value is expected in the Field that does not match the value given, so you must include an additional search for the Empty set as NULL is not a value

{panel:title=Not a Jira bug| borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
(i) This is not a Jira core bug, ticket created to track the problem and for transparency. 
At this stage, we believe the problem is related to MySQL: _for some reason MySQL chooses the wrong execution plan and doesn't use an index in optimal way_. That makes SQL execution slow. That being said, we will keep the ticket open for some time to monitor the problem. 
{panel}

h3. Summary
As part of Lexorank rebalancing, each rank value needs to be updated in {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK}} table.  At the same time, individual ranking operation has _1500 ms_ timeout for rank lock. 
Due to slow DB operation, issue ranking operation fails to save new rank since rank lock expires.  That makes Lexorank rebalancing process stall, usually you will see no progress in UI. Please note that situation is different to JSWSERVER-15703 


h3. Environment
* Large JIRA instance: 1M+ issue 
** more specific large {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK}} table
* We identified problem for *MySQL only*, other DBs might be also affected, but not reported so far.  

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Run Lexorank rebalancing 
# Monitor progress 

h3. Expected Results
* Lexorank rebalancing runs continuously and finishes successful. 
* SQL executions is fast:
{noformat}
SELECT FIELD_ID,ID,ISSUE_ID,LOCK_HASH,LOCK_TIME,RANK,TYPE FROM AO_60DB71_LEXORANK WHERE FIELD_ID = ? AND BUCKET = ? ORDER BY RANK ASC LIMIT 1; 
SELECT FIELD_ID,ID,ISSUE_ID,LOCK_HASH,LOCK_TIME,RANK,TYPE FROM AO_60DB71_LEXORANK WHERE FIELD_ID = ? AND BUCKET = ? ORDER BY RANK DESC LIMIT 1;
{noformat}

h3. Actual Results
* Lexorank rebalancing stalls
* Issue ranking operation fails to save new rank since rank lock expires
* SQL executions is slow

h3. Notes
* To enable logging set _DEBUG_ for {{com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.lexorank}} and {{com.atlassian.greenhopper.manager.lexorank}}
* Example of logging:
{noformat}
